      "start": 13.34,
      "end": 14.8,
      "text": "Recorded by Vicki Barber.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-004",
      "start": 15.82,
      "end": 16.64,
      "text": "Asop's Fables.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-005",
      "start": 17.62,
      "end": 18.64,
      "text": "The Man and the Lion.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-006",
      "start": 20.16,
      "end": 26.28,
      "text": "A man and a lion were companions on a journey, and in the course of conversation they began",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-007",
      "start": 26.28,
      "end": 32.82,
      "text": "to boast about their prowess, and each claimed to be superior to the other in strength and",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-008",
      "start": 32.82,
      "end": 33.2,
      "text": "courage.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-009",
      "start": 34.08,
      "end": 39.2,
      "text": "They were still arguing with some heat when they came to a crossroad, where there was",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-010",
      "start": 39.2,
      "end": 42.02,
      "text": "a statue of a man strangling a lion.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-011",
      "start": 42.58,
      "end": 44.94,
      "text": "There, said the man triumphantly.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-012",
      "start": 45.42,
      "end": 46.12,
      "text": "Look at that!",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-013",
      "start": 46.64,
      "end": 49.62,
      "text": "Doesn't that prove to you that we are stronger than you?",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-014",
      "start": 50.16,
      "end": 53.44,
      "text": "Not so fast, my friend, said the lion.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-015",
      "start": 53.44,
      "end": 56.06,
      "text": "That is only your view of the case.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-016",
      "start": 56.88,
      "end": 63.4,
      "text": "If we lions could make statues, you may be sure that in most of them you would see the",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-017",
      "start": 63.4,
      "end": 64.1,
      "text": "man underneath.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-018",
      "start": 65.68,
      "end": 67.8,
      "text": "There are two sides to every question.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-019",
      "start": 68.76,
      "end": 71.08,
      "text": "End of the man and the lion.",
      "note": ""
    }
  ],
